text.tspan: images need to have their xlink:href property be
specified relative to the SVG file location.
In addition, they need an src property that is
specifed relative to the root web directory.
So to give an example:
xlink:href = "../images/image.png"
src = "./images/image.png"
Note the usage of single vs double dots.
These images have the
correct properties.

Currently, only paths with straight sides are supported. Paths can be closed or open. The last point on the
path connects to the first point on the path. There is no limit to how many points a path may have.
You can give the path object an optional "speed" attribute that will control how fast the platform moves in
pixels per millisecond.
You need to group a rectangle with the path object. Select both objects and type Ctrl-G to group them.
all rect objects on the spike layer are interpreted as spike fields. The number of spikes per unit lenght is constant and defined in the code.
The hight of the spikes is determined by the height of the rectange.
All rect objects on the grapple layer are
interpreted as grapple points.
The grapple point is centered on the
rect.

Welcome to the Cheetah
tutorial!
The Cheetah is easy to use,
first, find the Cheetah by
tapping 'F'.
Press and hold 'D'. Your
cheetah will hop once, then
stay still. Auto jump is now
enabled.
Press and hold the Right
arrow key to run at a jump.
When your cheetah reaches
the edge, he will auto jump,
as long as you are still
holding down 'D', that is.
Congratulations! That's
all there is too it!
